Interface Identifiable

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    EventsController, ResourceBuilder
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Activator, AddOn, ContentGenerator, Event, LocalEventManager, OutputExtension, OutputManager, OutputPlugin

    public interface Identifiable
    Makes a class identifiable by forcing implementations to set an ID.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods Default Methods

    • Method Detail

      • getID

        java.lang.String getID()
        An ID must always be unique. A Class like Activator or OutputPlugin can just provide their .class.getCanonicalName() If you have to implement this interface multiple times, just concatenate unique Strings to .class.getCanonicalName()
        Returns:
        A String containing an ID

      • isOwner

        default boolean isOwner(Identification identification)
        checks whether this instance is the owner of this Identification
        Parameters:
        identification - the identification to check
        Returns:
        true if the same, false if not
